data.title: Dianne Rodriguez Obituary 2023

data.text:
Services are scheduled for 10 am Saturday, August 12 Our Lady of Grace Catholic Church for Dianne G. Rodriguez of Artesia, New Mexico.

Ms. Rodriguez, 42, died on August 7, 2023 in Artesia.

Father Vijay will officiate at the services with burial to follow at Woodbine Cemetery.

A rosary is also scheduled for 6:30 pm on Friday. Visitation will be at Terpening & Son Mortuary from 2 to 4 pm on Friday.

Pallbearer's will be Nathaniel Zarazua, Anthony Armendariz, Enrique Armendariz, Sammy Rodriguez, Gabriel Rodriguez, and Joshua Rodriguez. Honorary pallbearer's will be Pete Perez, Sergio Paz, Daniel Rodriguez, Jason Castleberry, Ricky Armendariz, Estevan Rodriguez, Edmundo Valenzuela, Robert Fernandez, and Sergio Paz III.

Dianne was born on January 10, 1981 in Hobbs, New Mexico; the daughter of Sammy Rodriguez and Anita Brewer.

Dianne loved to go night fishing, going to the casino, spending time in the mountains and most importantly spending all the time with her grandbabies, who were her whole world. She was a very hard worker who loved to cook. She was the absolute best grandma ever and would do anything for her babies. She loved her family and was there for each and every one of them whenever they needed her.

She was preceded in death by her grandparents Felix and Lucinda Garcia, and Pete and Carmen Rodriguez, uncles Felix Garcia Jr., and Harvey Rodriguez, and aunt Rosalinda Rodriguez.

Survivors include her father Sammy Rodriguez spouse Rebecca Rodriguez; mother Anita Brewer spouse David Brewer; Children Nathaniel Zarazua spouse Alexandra Flores, Anthony Armendariz spouse Alyssa Hernandez, Enrique Armendariz, Adrianna Zarazua spouse Sergio Paz Jr., and Jasmine Armendariz; siblings Sammy Rodriquez Jr. spouse Sarah Rodriguez, Gabriel Rodriguez spouse Jody Rodriguez, Joshua Rodriguez spouse Delaney Rodriguez, sisters Samantha Fernandez spouse Robert Fernandez, Claudia Armendariz, Danielle Castleberry spouse Jason Castleberry, Abigail Rodriguez spouse Daniel Rodriguez, Nakita Alvarado spouse Estevan Rodriguez and Ari Ortiz; also by grandchildren Sergio Paz III and Mia Paz, and numerous nieces and nephews.
